<title>USA: ADR REPORT - Canadian Pacific higher.</title>
<headline>ADR REPORT - Canadian Pacific higher.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-06-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>Canadian Pacific Ltd rose Tuesday above a 12-month high to stand out among foreign shares and American depositary receipts (ADRs).</p>
<p>The Alberta-based conglomerate was up 1-3/8, to 28-3/4, in late morning, above a 12-month closing high of 28-5/8.</p>
<p>The increase followed the company's announcement after the market closed Monday that it was selling its interest in transportation and waste-management company Laidlaw Inc for $722 million in net proceeds.</p>
<p>Canadian Pacific said it expected to post a gain of $199 million from the sale.  </p>
<p>Among other active foreign issues, Bermuda's Globalstar Telecommunications Ltd rose 5/8 to 31-7/8 and Singaporean software company Creative Technology Ltd was up one to 17-5/8.</p>
<p>Canada's Abacan Resource Corp eased 1/16 to 1-15/16. Britain's Glaxo Wellcome Plc fell 1/4 to 41-1/4 after it announced it had created a genetics directorate to boost its research and development in the field.</p>
<p>((-- Wall Street desk (212) 859-1730))</p>
